This plugin allows you to over-ride the default browser alert() implementation so that you can style it however you want.

Usage:
Include the plugin JS and CSS files in your page. Change the location of the modal-1px.png graphic in your CSS file if necessary (default: modal-1px.png). Call the following on your page:

$().customAlert({
    alertTitle : 'Notice!',
    alertOk	 : 'OK',
    draggable	 : false
});

Options:
	alertTitle: The title shown in the alert box,
	alertOk: OK button text,
	draggable: Set to true to make the alert box draggable (you will need jQuery UI for this to work)

If you need to use the default browser alert then call defaultAlert().

Let me know if you have any problems!

